CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 8, 1947, pg. 17, reads: "A Family Celebration - The home of Mrs. Lela Terry of Burrows Street was the scene recently of a dinner party given in her honor. Among the members of her family who attended the event were three daughters, three sons, two daughters-in-law, three sons-in-law, and nineteen grandchildren. Also present were Mrs. Lula Deakings and the Rev. and Mrs. Thomas H. Spotwood. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Party in honor of Lela Terry surrounded by her family, and friends, including Lulu Deakings, Rev. Thomas H. Spotwood, and Mrs. Spotwood, in Terry home on Burrows Street
